prompt: I am a new hire.How do I enroll in benefits?
text:
Enrollment is completed through SmartBen, which activates the Thursday after your start date.   

Log into PeopleHub and navigate to the US Benefits Enrollment tile under "My Info." 

Please visit the US New Hire Benefit Enrollment and Benefits Enrollment Resources pages for more details.

prompt: I am a new employee.Where can I find new hire resources
text: Please check New Employee Onboarding Checklist.

prompt: Where can I find my Pega ID/ Employee ID/ Global ID PUID ?
text: On yourPeopleHub profile, click on your picture on the top right corner, and the ID is next to your name in parentheses.

prompt: What is PeopleHub ?
text:
PeopleHub is Pega's HRIS system where personnel and job information is stored for critical purposes such as Employee and Manager Self-Service. PeopleHub also helps the People Team manage processes around recruitment, applicant tracking, learning management, attendance, time management, talent cultivation, and benefits. 

PeopleHub provides employees and managers with quick and easy access to valuable information that empowers a culture of self-service, providing you the data needed to keep up with business needs. To name a few: 

employment details 
address updates 
name changes 
benefit elections 
bank details 
verifications of employment 
team members 
org chart 
Check it out!

prompt: I can't access PeopleHub or specific section of PeopleHub.
text:
Pega employees can log into PeopleHub by typing peoplehub.pega.com in your browser.  

Logging into the VPN will also ensure proper access. If that does not work, please clear the cookies/cache from your browser. Review these steps for further assistance.

prompt: I recently moved How do I change my address?
text:
To update your address in PeopleHub:

Log into PeopleHub and navigate to the "My Profile" tile under the "My Info" section.
Click on the "Personal Information" tab which will navigate you to the "Address Information" section.
Edit by clicking on the pencil icon.
pencil icon on PeopleHub
Enter the effective date along with the changes of your address and click the "Save" button.
This is also a great time to double check the rest of your personal information details!

Please note that if you are moving states or countries, your work location needs to be changed as well. Please ensure your manager processes this Job Information Change on your PeopleHub employee profile. Additionally, ensure your tax withholdings are updated on your regional payroll system.

prompt: I got married.How do I change my marital status and/or name?
text:
To update your marital status/ name in PeopleHub:

Log into PeopleHub and navigate to the "My Profile" tile under the "My Info" section.
Click on the "Personal Information" tab and then scroll down to another "Personal Information" section.
Edit by clicking on the pencil icon.
 
pencil icon on PeopleHub
Enter the effective date along with your personal changes (marital status, name, emergency contact) and click the "Save" button.
This is a great time to double check the rest of your personal information!

Please remember to update your tax forms if applicable. Additionally, if your spouse is moving to Pegas insurance plan or they are becoming a new beneficiary, please review your regions life event process through our Global Benefits Portal or the Benefits section of this FAQ page.

prompt: How do I view the status of my pending requests?
text: After logging into PeopleHub, scroll down to the Additional Resources section of the homepage. From there, find and click on the View My Pending Requests tile and you will be redirected to a new screen where you can view and manage all of your pending requests.

prompt: I am a manager and need to make job changes to my employee's profile
text: Please see the Managers Corner section of the FAQ and visit the Manager Self-Service page for additional guides

prompt: Which healthcare plan should I choose?
text: If you need help comparing the medical plans and deciding which one is right for you, please leverage PLANselect our medical decision tool or you can reach out to Health Advocate for assistance.

prompt: How can I confirm my benefits elections?
text:
From the PeopleHub homepage click on the US Benefits Enrollment tile, which will redirect to SmartBen.  

On your SmartBen homepage under the header named MY BENEFITS, click View Enrollment Confirmation to see your current benefit elections.

prompt: I am having issues accessing SmartBen
text:
After ensuring you are logged into the VPN and using a Chrome browser, log into PeopleHub and navigate to US Benefits Enrollment tile under My Info.   

If this is your first week at Pega, please wait until your account is activated on the first Thursday after your start date.  

If the issue persists, please use the following credentials to log in and alert peoplehub@pega.com to investigate the issue further: 
 

Username: PEGA+9-digit SSN (Ex: PEGA123456789) 
Password: Date of Birth in MMDDYYYY format (Ex: For DOB of April 3rd, 2020, use 04032020)

prompt: How do I submit time off?
text:
Please use this page to determine which time tracking application you should use and detailed recordings on the usage of each application.  

PeopleHub: Go to PeopleHub  My Employee Profile  Time Off  Go to Time Off  Create Absence  Select the drop-down list titled Time Type and you will see the different timecodes available to you. Choose the most appropriate one and fill out the details before submitting. 

Time App: If you do enter your hours every week, you will go to the Pega Portal  Submit/Approve Timesheets  Record time in the Time App  Enter Time  type in the time code that is appropriate (by referencing the drop-down list in PeopleHub) and enter your hours this way.

prompt: My vacation balance is incorrect on the Time App.How is it calculated?
text:
You can see how your vacation balance is calculated by logging into the Time App and clicking on "Time Off Balance" from the left-hand navigation menu.   

Inside "Leave Summary, you can click on "Leave Taken" to expand it and see a list of all leaves that have been approved this year.   

If any entries on this list are incorrect, please send an email to peoplehub@pega.com with the list of requested changes.

prompt: My balance is incorrect on PeopleHub. How is it calculated?
text: From the Time Off page in PeopleHub, click Show All under the Balances section. You can then see your balances for any date.  Additionally, you can select Account View to see a more detailed description of your balances showing what you have earned, taken, and planned for any date.

prompt: Can I enter time before my employment start date on the Time App?
text: There is a restriction that prevents you from entering time before your start date.  If you created a timesheet that ends before your start date, enter a ticket to have the timesheet closed and removed from your worklist.

prompt: I dont see a company holiday on my Time App timesheet
text:
Please try adding the holiday to your timesheet under the correct holiday timecode for your geographic region: 

PEGA-PEG-HR-Time off APAC-Time Off-Public Holiday 
PEGA-PEG-HR-Time Off US-Time Off-Company Paid Holiday 
PEGA-PEG-HR-Time Off CAN-Time Off-Company Paid Holiday 
PEGA-PEG-HR-Time off EU-Time Off-Bank Holiday 
PEGA-PEG-HR-TIME OFF IN-Time Off-Holiday 
PEGA-PEG-HR-TIME OFF LATAM-Time Off-Company Paid Holiday 
If the hours next to this timecode are greyed out, please enter a ticket in SM using the category.

prompt: How do I submit bereavement leave?
text:
Please notify your manager and record the absence on the timekeeping application you regularly use by typing Bereavement Leave on the Timesheet app and finding Bereavement Leave on the drop-down menu on PeopleHub.  

Pega offers up two weeks off for immediate family and five days for other relatives. As a reminder, immediate family is defined as a spouse, domestic partner, child, or parent. Relatives (non-immediate family) in this policy are defined as grandparents, siblings, and in-laws. 

Please review our Bereavement Leave page to find out how we can further support you through this difficult time.

prompt: I am unable to edit the hours on a timesheet I am approving on the Time App
text: In some cases, you might be unable to make modifications directly to an employees timesheet.  If this happens, you should reject any time that needs to be modified and provide justification in the comments section.

prompt: How do I change my personal information on the payroll provider(i.e,. UKG)?
text:
All changes to your personal information held on the payroll vendor (i.e., UKG) must be changed in PeopleHub. The changes will be reflected within two weeks of being made.

For India ONLY: Please email payrollindiateam@pega.com with the required changes on the payroll vendor portal with document proof.  Regarding tax declaration, the DKM portal will be open between 1-15th every month to make changes to the tax declaration under Investment details.

prompt: How do I obtain an employment verification letter?
text:
Please log into PeopleHubto download your Verification of Employment (VoE) letter in English. A guide can be found on our PeopleHub Self-Service page under the Employee section.  

US employees: you also have the option to utilize the Work Number. Simply provide the verifier with Work Numbers website and they can access that information 24-7. More information on the Work Number can be found on the US Payroll page.

prompt: When do I receive the one-time stipend to set up my home office?
text:
Once all the required training is completed, the stipend payment will be included in the next regularly scheduled payroll cycle following your probation period, if any. This varies by country but is typically 120 days from your start date. 

The training request is sent via training@pega.com and KnowBe4. The training link is also available through the Pega Portal InfoSec page under Mandatory Training  Cybersecurity Training.

prompt: When do I get paid ?
text:
Australia	Last Thursday of every month
Brazil	25th of every month
Canada	Semi-monthly
India	Final working day of each month
Italy	27th day of each calendar month
Japan	25th of every month
Other EMEA regions	Final working day of each month
Other APJ regions	Final working day of each month
US	
You need to work a full pay cycle in order to be active in the payroll system. Our payroll cycles are every two weeks, so if the payday is less than a week away from your start date, you will be on the following pay date. Your first check will include all time from your start date. For salaried employees, your first check (for those starting in the middle of a cycle) is commonly for 120 hours. For hourly employees that are paid in arrears, they will be paid for their first week only, which is usually for 40 hours. 

For more information, please visit the US Payroll page.

prompt: Where can I find my paycheck/paystub in US?
text:
As of January 8, 2021, you can access the new UKG (formerly known as UltiPro) system via single sign-on (SSO) from your laptop or via the UKG UltiPro mobile app. Using the UKG portal, you will be able to access your current 2021 and beyond pay statements, and W2s, change tax withholdings and calculate different pay-altering scenarios. 

To access UKG:  

For first time log-in:  

Once logged into Pegas VPN, go to: pega.ultipro.com. 
You will immediately be directed to a page where you can change your password. 
Enter your birthdate as your current password (in MMDDYYYY format). 
Enter a new password of your choosing by following the password requirements on the screen. 
Click OK to access the UltiPro portal. 
From personal computer:  

When you enter the URL (pega.ultipro.com) on a non-Pega device, use your Pega email and Pega login.
It will run you through our VPN authentication connection to your UKG site. 
For other scenarios:  

Once you log in for the first time, you will be able to log in directly via Pegas SSO (Single Sign-On).  
UKG UltiPro App: 

Download the UKG UltiPro app on your Apple or Android device.  
The company access code is: Pegasystems  
Click on Use SSO Credentials to enter. You will have the same access and capabilities on the mobile app as you do on the web portal. 
To access 2020 and prior pay statements and W2s from ADP: 

Go to https://workforcenow.adp.com/public/index.htm (same URL and credentials previously used). 
You will have access to these pay statements and W2s for three years (expires Dec. 31, 2023). 
For more information, please visit the US Payroll page.

prompt: Where can I find my paycheck/paystub in India?
text:
To access your recent payslips, please log into DKM Portal at https://www.dkmonline.co.in/Login.aspx.

Navigate to Access your documents/Home page > View/Download Payslips. From there, youre able to view and download your posted payslips. 

For tax slips, please go to Access your documents/ Home page > View/Download tax slip. 

Additionally, you can use MyPeopleDoc as described for All Other Regions (select the last tab titled All Other Regions for further instructions).

prompt: Where can I find my paycheck/paystub in Poland?
text:
After your first months pay, youll have access to ActivPayroll. You can view your payslips and year-end statements there by following the instructions below. 

First-time users: you should have received an activation email from noreply@activpayroll.com with the subject line Welcome to activ8. The email includes instructions on how to activate your account.  

After you sign in, you can view your statements by clicking on ePay on the left-hand menu to expand the ePay selections. Click View Payslips or Annual Statements. Your most recent statement will be displayed under the Latest Pay Slip or Latest Annual Statement label.

Your historical payslips will be displayed under the Previous Pay Slips or Previous Annual Statement label. They can be filtered by year using the drop-down option provided. Click Show Report. The downloaded file will be a PDF file. A link to a free PDF viewing application is provided at the bottom of the page.

prompt: Where can I find my paycheck/paystub in UK?
text:
After your first months pay, youll have access to ADP to view your payslips along with Form P60. Form P11D is emailed to your Pega email in early June. 

First-time users: please note that the following information will be requested:

Self Service Registration Passcode: Pegasystem-33558857 
Employee Number: Can be found on PeopleHub > My Profile   
National Insurance Number 
Date of Birth 
Post Code (of home address)

prompt: Where can I find my paycheck/paystub in Turkey?
text: Your paycheck will be emailed to you each month by your payroll provider.

prompt: How do I enroll in ESPP program
text: Enrollment opens at specific times of the year. More information on the different enrollment options can be found on the Equity page.

prompt: What is my Global ID/ PUID as requested by Morgan Stanley?
text: Morgan Stanleys Global ID is your Pega ID (the ID you use to log in to your computer).

prompt: I need to change my address on my Morgan Stanley account
text: Address changes can be completed through your PeopleHub profile. Updates will be reflected on your Morgan Stanley profile within up to 30 days.

prompt: Where can I find learning and development resources?
text: Please visit the Learning@Pega page to find out more.

prompt: I completed a course in Pega Academy/ new Hire Compliance Training, and it isn't showing as completed in Learning Gateway
text: The course(s) you have referenced are synced with the Learning Gateway monthly. You should see these showing as completed in the first week of next month.

prompt: How do I access the courses?
text:
All employees have access to the courses within the Learning Gateway.  

To access the Learning Gateway, login to PeopleHub and click on the Learning tile under My Career.
 
To list courses from a particular provider, click on Browse all courses in the Find Learning tile and select the provider in the Source option.

prompt: I dont see the learning tile on my PeopleHub dashboard.
text: In the upper-left dropdown of the PeopleHub homepage, there should be an option called Learning, which is the link to the Learning Gateway. If you do not see this, please take a screenshot of your PeopleHub homepage and send it to peoplehub@pega.com.

prompt: I have attended an instructor-led course that is not showing as completed/still appearing in my "to-Do Items" on my PeopleHub dashboard
text: Once an instructor-led course is completed, the instructor is required to mark the attendance of each delegate. There can be a delay of approximately one week for this to be reflected in your Learning Gateway.

prompt: I can see courses directly in Udemy/edX/Skillsoft that are not appearing as available courses in learning Gateway.
text: New courses added to each of these platforms each week are synced to the Learning Gateway weekly. Any new course will appear in the Learning Gateway by the start of next week.

prompt: Where can I find specific resources for people managers?
text: The People Managers Toolkit offers you the resources you need to engage with your employees throughout their entire journey at Pega, from finding the right hire to delivering difficult messages or retaining your top performers.

prompt: How do I request additional headcount?
text:
Pega uses position management to think about our workforce. Each job (or position) is seen as an empty chair and employees sit in these chairs. From time to time, you may need to request new headcount. This may be because you need an additional seat on your team or perhaps an employee has left, and you want to refill that seat.

These requests may all be submitted using the Position Org chart in PeopleHub. For more information on position management and how to make these requests, review the Position Management section of the People Manager's Toolkit.

Please contact your TAP regarding any anticipatory or confidential needs for People team assistance. Please do not open any confidential or anticipatory positions directly.

prompt: How do I bring in a non employee?
text:
Pegas People Function, in partnership with the Legal and Procurement departments, are responsible for the initiation, review, onboarding, and offboarding of non-employee resources that are not directly engaged in services with Pegas clients. In addition, Pegas non-employee program assists managers with the recruitment of temporary resources to augment their staff in order to meet their business needs. 

Before you start the process of engaging a temporary resource, you need to ensure all the costs/ budgets have been vetted and approved internally by all the appropriate parties including Finance. An explanation of the process can be found on the Non-Employee (Contractor) Resources page.

prompt: How do I ensure a successful onboarding of my new employee?
text: Review the Onboard Your Employee guide to learn what to do before your new hire arrives, how to set up your employee in PeopleHub, and what to do when your new hire starts.

prompt: I am unable to edit the hours on a timesheet I am approving
text: In some cases, you might be unable to make modifications directly to an employees timesheet.  If this happens, you should reject any time that needs to be modified and provide justification in the comments section.

prompt: How do I give recognition?
text:
Employees who drive client success and go above and beyond in modeling Pega's Values and Success Behaviors can be acknowledged through our ongoing Talent Recognition Platform or our Employee of the Month Program. 

Review Pega's Talent Recognition Program on the Pega Portal for additional details and instructions.

prompt: When do the annual performance and compensation reviews occur?
text:
Please refer to the People Process Calendar for information on when compensation programs happen throughout the year. 

You can also use the Manager's Talent Cultivation Review Guide to assist you with the annual review process.

prompt: My employee is leaving the team or company. What steps do I have to take?
text: The Transition Your Employee page covers everything you need to know as you look to move your employee to a new team or assist them with leaving Pega.

prompt: How do I view the status of my pending requests?
text: After logging into PeopleHub, scroll down to the Additional Resources section of the homepage. From there, find and click on the View My Pending Requests tile and you will be redirected to a new screen where you can view and manage all of your pending requests.
